Probably he meant "без пощады" [bjez pashjady], but what did he mean?..

Everyone were wrong except this dude.

Small thing you can know:

When Russians began to colonize Kamchatka peninsula they discovered serious problems with native tribes.

Basicly, none of the colonist were soldiers, just scientists, prisoners and poor people.

So, they tried to attack somewhat suddenly, because they need at least a tiny bit of tactical dominance.

And when you hear "Без пощады!", it means everyone are going to be slaughtered with no remorse or sorrow, eldery, women, children or men, it doesn't matter, they need to be dead.

And other case is when this means "I know no sorry" which means that you won't forgive, whether he/she/it is praying, crying or whatever people do.
